1
00:00:13,833 --> 00:00:16,133
<i>I can stand now, Hazel,
I can walk again.</i>

2
00:00:16,267 --> 00:00:17,367
<i>I can fight you
if I have to.</i>

3
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:18,433
<i> And I'm telling you.</i>

4
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:20,667
<i>Don't you dare lay a hand
on my kids!</i>

5
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,867
<i>Cousin, she'll recover
soon, right?</i>

6
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,233
<i>I can't guarantee anything,
cousin.</i>

7
00:00:25,367 --> 00:00:29,633
<i>We can work on a treatment
modality specific to her case.</i>

8
00:00:29,767 --> 00:00:32,533
<i>So, I won't fully recover
after all.</i>

9
00:00:32,667 --> 00:00:37,000
<i>Dear God,
please give me strength.</i>

10
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:40,367
<i> Heal me for my family.</i>

11
00:00:47,967 --> 00:00:49,767
Dad, Andrea took Coleen
to school

12
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,700
before heading to FMP.

13
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:53,433
I'll follow her
there later, okay?

14
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:57,733
Jeff...

15
00:00:57,867 --> 00:00:59,333
maybe you can call
your mom.

16
00:00:59,467 --> 00:01:00,633
I just need to talk to her.

17
00:01:02,433 --> 00:01:05,000
Dad, maybe the conference
already started?

18
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:06,633
No, just try calling.

19
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:08,167
Maybe she'll answer.

20
00:01:12,267 --> 00:01:13,300
Okay, Dad.

21
00:01:14,533 --> 00:01:15,433
I'll call her from outside, Dad.

22
00:01:15,567 --> 00:01:17,100
The signal's bad here.

23
00:01:17,233 --> 00:01:18,700
- Yes, sure.
- Huh?

24
00:01:32,533 --> 00:01:34,067
<i> Hello? Jeffrey?</i>

25
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,767
Mom...

26
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:37,700
Mom, Dad wants to talk
to you.

27
00:01:37,833 --> 00:01:39,133
<i> I want to talk to him too,</i>

28
00:01:39,267 --> 00:01:43,133
but he might find out
I'm here in Davao.

29
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:45,000
Mom, I don't know
what to say anymore.

30
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:48,400
Dad thinks you're at
a conference in Batangas.

31
00:01:48,533 --> 00:01:49,633
<i> I'm sorry, son.</i>

32
00:01:49,767 --> 00:01:51,633
<i> You were forced to lie.</i>

33
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,400
Jeff?

34
00:01:56,767 --> 00:01:58,133
Jeff? Son?

35
00:01:58,267 --> 00:01:59,767
Is that your mom?

36
00:02:03,333 --> 00:02:04,833
Oh, hello, Felma.

37
00:02:04,967 --> 00:02:08,333
I'm glad you're finally back.

38
00:02:08,467 --> 00:02:09,333
Yes.

39
00:02:09,467 --> 00:02:10,500
I was actually planning
to surprise you,

40
00:02:10,633 --> 00:02:12,367
<i> but you weren't here.</i>

41
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:14,867
Felma, I really miss you.

42
00:02:15,033 --> 00:02:17,133
I miss you, too, Manuel.

43
00:02:17,267 --> 00:02:18,533
How many more days
are you staying there?

44
00:02:18,667 --> 00:02:19,700
When are you coming home?

45
00:02:19,833 --> 00:02:21,133
Ah? Oh...

46
00:02:21,267 --> 00:02:22,233
Oh my, Manuel.

47
00:02:22,367 --> 00:02:24,500
Ah, Paz is calling me.

48
00:02:24,633 --> 00:02:26,333
The conference
is about to start.

49
00:02:26,467 --> 00:02:28,633
Let's just talk next time, okay?

50
00:02:28,767 --> 00:02:30,500
Hello? Felma?

51
00:02:30,633 --> 00:02:31,767
Felma?

52
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:33,033
Hello...

53
00:02:37,267 --> 00:02:39,333
She said the conference
is starting.

54
00:02:40,667 --> 00:02:42,267
That was such a cliffhanger.

55
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:53,967
Friend.

56
00:02:56,633 --> 00:02:57,800
Hazel?

57
00:03:02,433 --> 00:03:03,367
What's that?

58
00:03:06,167 --> 00:03:07,200
Friend, it's so early,

59
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:09,567
and you're already drinking
on an empty stomach.

60
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:13,167
Just leave me alone.

61
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:14,633
Leave me alone.

62
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,400
- Oh!
- That's not a solution

63
00:03:16,533 --> 00:03:18,467
to your problem,
give it to me!

64
00:03:21,067 --> 00:03:23,533
And what is the solution then?

65
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:26,133
You know what?

66
00:03:26,267 --> 00:03:27,967
Instead of nagging me...

67
00:03:29,867 --> 00:03:31,433
why don't you think...

68
00:03:32,833 --> 00:03:34,467
think of a way for me...

69
00:03:35,867 --> 00:03:37,567
to get my husband back?

70
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:40,200
You can no longer
get Manuel back.

71
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:41,467
Alice.

72
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,367
I thought you were on my side?

73
00:03:46,267 --> 00:03:48,767
You're doubting me now?

74
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:50,800
Come on, Hazel.

75
00:03:50,933 --> 00:03:54,233
From the very start,
I supported you.

76
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,933
Even when I didn't agree
with everything.

77
00:03:56,067 --> 00:03:57,233
Because you're my friend.

78
00:03:57,367 --> 00:03:59,433
But here's a real talk,

79
00:03:59,567 --> 00:04:01,167
your husband already knows
the truth.

80
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:03,733
He's with Felma now.

81
00:04:03,867 --> 00:04:05,300
You're not getting him back.

82
00:04:05,433 --> 00:04:06,867
You need to accept that.

83
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:08,567
No.

84
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:11,633
There has to be another way.

85
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:14,433
So, what now?

86
00:04:14,567 --> 00:04:16,333
Are you going
to pay someone...

87
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:17,200
again?

88
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:19,233
Threaten them?

89
00:04:19,367 --> 00:04:21,467
Hazel, you've done everything.

90
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:23,900
You played the villain,
you played the saint.

91
00:04:24,033 --> 00:04:25,900
You were one step away
from hurting yourself

92
00:04:26,033 --> 00:04:28,067
just to make Manuel feel guilty.

93
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:49,067
Ouch.

94
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:51,100
- Dad!
- Dad!

95
00:04:51,233 --> 00:04:52,500
Oh.

96
00:04:57,567 --> 00:04:58,467
Hi, Dad!

97
00:04:58,600 --> 00:04:59,867
- Wow, nice!
- Hi!

98
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:04,633
Dad, it feels so strange
seeing you walk again.

99
00:05:06,333 --> 00:05:08,067
You'll get used to it.

100
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,500
Dad, we have a surprise for you.

101
00:05:09,633 --> 00:05:11,400
Oh?

102
00:05:11,533 --> 00:05:14,167
- Wow!
- That's amazing!

103
00:05:14,300 --> 00:05:16,367
So you won't have
a hard time anymore, Dad.

104
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:18,567
- And so you'll recover faster.
- Yes.

105
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:27,000
You're right.

106
00:05:30,467 --> 00:05:31,500
Maybe...

107
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:36,600
if they see me helpless,

108
00:05:36,767 --> 00:05:38,400
especially Manuel

109
00:05:40,300 --> 00:05:41,700
he'll come back to me.

110
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:44,467
Maybe...

111
00:05:45,767 --> 00:05:47,033
that's the moment...

112
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:49,633
he'll come back for me.

113
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:51,967
That's it.

114
00:05:52,100 --> 00:05:52,800
You're brilliant.

115
00:05:52,933 --> 00:05:54,700
Friend, you're brilliant.

116
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:56,500
So brilliant.

117
00:05:56,633 --> 00:05:57,900
Are you losing your mind?

118
00:05:58,033 --> 00:05:58,800
What is wrong with you?

119
00:05:58,933 --> 00:06:00,900
Friend.

120
00:06:01,033 --> 00:06:02,367
Hurt me.

121
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:06,100
- No.
- Friend, hurt me.

122
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:07,433
No!

123
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:20,733
Friend! Wait.

124
00:06:20,867 --> 00:06:21,867
Hold on.

125
00:06:22,767 --> 00:06:23,933
Just injure me.

126
00:06:24,067 --> 00:06:24,900
What?

127
00:06:25,033 --> 00:06:26,333
Just a little.

128
00:06:26,467 --> 00:06:27,333
Just a little.

129
00:06:27,467 --> 00:06:29,967
Hurt me so when Manuel sees

130
00:06:30,100 --> 00:06:33,300
or hears that I'm hospitalized,

131
00:06:33,433 --> 00:06:34,633
maybe he'll come back.

132
00:06:34,767 --> 00:06:37,100
- Of course, he'll come back.
- No!

133
00:06:37,233 --> 00:06:38,300
Just... come on.

134
00:06:38,433 --> 00:06:39,133
Hurt me.

135
00:06:39,267 --> 00:06:39,900
Wait.

136
00:06:40,033 --> 00:06:40,867
Just a little.

137
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,133
Come on!

138
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:43,833
I said give it to me!

139
00:06:43,967 --> 00:06:46,233
Hazel, wake up!

140
00:06:46,367 --> 00:06:48,600
Is this how desperate
you've become?

141
00:06:48,733 --> 00:06:51,033
You're turning me
into a criminal?

142
00:06:51,167 --> 00:06:52,767
Hazel, Manuel is gone.

143
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:54,400
Do you understand?

144
00:06:54,533 --> 00:06:55,600
He's not coming back.

145
00:06:55,733 --> 00:06:57,033
He's not.

146
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:13,767
Thank you.

147
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:16,600
- Oh! Nice.
- This one's included, too, Dad.

148
00:07:16,767 --> 00:07:18,933
I'm really lucky
to have you guys.

149
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:23,500
All right, because of that,
it's groupie time.

150
00:07:24,467 --> 00:07:27,367
Groupie? Okay.

151
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:29,133
- There!
- There!

152
00:07:29,267 --> 00:07:30,667
Nice!

153
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,233
- Cute.
- Looks good.

154
00:07:32,367 --> 00:07:33,233
I think this one's better.

155
00:07:33,367 --> 00:07:35,433
Hey, don't crop me out.

156
00:07:35,567 --> 00:07:37,033
Oh, what time is it now?

157
00:07:37,167 --> 00:07:39,567
Maybe we can call your mom.

158
00:07:41,733 --> 00:07:43,100
Later, Dad.

159
00:07:43,233 --> 00:07:46,233
Our plan is to go out first.

160
00:07:46,367 --> 00:07:49,167
We'll check out the newly
opened mall nearby.

161
00:07:50,233 --> 00:07:50,933
Yes, that's right.

162
00:07:51,067 --> 00:07:51,833
Let's go, let's go.

163
00:07:51,967 --> 00:07:52,667
Come on, Dad.

164
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:53,667
I'll just leave
my things inside.

165
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,167
Yes, sure.

166
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,933
- Let's go.
- All right, then.

167
00:08:19,967 --> 00:08:22,333
- Thank you.
- There.

168
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:23,700
Thank you.

169
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,667
What are you doing now?

170
00:08:32,133 --> 00:08:35,300
Oh... I'm emailing the bank.

171
00:08:35,433 --> 00:08:38,367
I'm asking for an updated
investment statement.

172
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:43,800
So I can organize the files
before handing them to Andrea.

173
00:08:45,533 --> 00:08:46,833
Felma...

174
00:08:46,967 --> 00:08:48,633
do you really have
to prioritize that?

175
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,900
Shouldn't you tell them
you're sick?

176
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:55,400
Or at least tell Manuel?

177
00:08:55,567 --> 00:08:57,567
Manuel just got back home.

178
00:08:59,733 --> 00:09:01,500
I don't want...

179
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:03,300
to worry him again.

180
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:05,167
Felma...

181
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:08,433
if you don't want them
to worry,

182
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:11,500
shouldn't you be getting
surgery?

183
00:09:11,633 --> 00:09:13,267
I've decided.

184
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,933
I'm not getting the surgery.

185
00:09:17,933 --> 00:09:19,033
Didang!

186
00:09:19,167 --> 00:09:20,933
- Miss Paz! Oh my!
- Oh?

187
00:09:21,067 --> 00:09:22,300
What's with your face, Didang?

188
00:09:22,433 --> 00:09:23,633
You look like you saw a ghost.

189
00:09:23,767 --> 00:09:25,133
Am I that ugly?

190
00:09:25,267 --> 00:09:25,900
Geez!

191
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:28,467
What happened to you, huh?

192
00:09:28,633 --> 00:09:30,000
What happened to you?

193
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:36,233
Man, the therapy really worked.

194
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:38,133
You can stand now.

195
00:09:38,267 --> 00:09:39,867
Manuel, what are you doing here?

196
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:40,900
How did you get back so fast?

197
00:09:41,033 --> 00:09:42,967
What are you doing here?

198
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:44,367
And where's Felma?

199
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:45,600
We came from Dumaguete.

200
00:09:45,733 --> 00:09:47,500
- Here...
- Wait, I thought

201
00:09:47,633 --> 00:09:50,033
you and Felma had a conference
in Batangas?

202
00:09:50,167 --> 00:09:51,633
Conference? Batangas?

203
00:09:51,767 --> 00:09:53,100
What are you talking about?

204
00:09:53,233 --> 00:09:56,933
I took leave because my auntie
had a party in Dumaguete.

205
00:09:57,067 --> 00:09:59,000
-Yes.
-See? I even brought something.

206
00:10:02,933 --> 00:10:04,867
You lied to me?

207
00:10:08,633 --> 00:10:10,167
So, where exactly
is your mother?

208
00:10:13,433 --> 00:10:14,267
What?

209
00:10:15,300 --> 00:10:17,000
You're not getting surgery?

210
00:10:17,133 --> 00:10:18,900
Didn't you hear what Emil said?

211
00:10:19,033 --> 00:10:21,167
If the tumor isn't removed,

212
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:22,600
it'll be hard for you, Felma.

213
00:10:23,633 --> 00:10:25,000
It won't be good for you.

214
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:26,400
Exactly.

215
00:10:26,533 --> 00:10:27,967
As long as I still can...

216
00:10:28,933 --> 00:10:31,067
I'm fixing things
with the bank first.

217
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:32,767
Then the FMP.

218
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:36,333
I'll talk to my lawyer, too.

219
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:39,133
So you're choosing all of that

220
00:10:39,267 --> 00:10:40,733
over your health?

221
00:10:40,867 --> 00:10:45,433
I'm choosing Manuel
and my kids, Noah.

222
00:10:45,567 --> 00:10:48,133
When all of this is done,

223
00:10:48,267 --> 00:10:51,467
that's when I'll think
about the surgery.

224
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:53,033
Isn't it?

225
00:10:53,167 --> 00:10:55,467
Your cousin said it himself.

226
00:10:55,600 --> 00:11:00,033
There's no guarantee
I'll fully recover.

227
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:05,933
Maybe I won't even make it
through the operation.

228
00:11:06,067 --> 00:11:10,400
At least if that happens,
everything's already in order.

229
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,900
My family won't
struggle anymore.

230
00:11:17,767 --> 00:11:19,867
Oh my! Oh my! Oh my!

231
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,000
Says the turkey!

232
00:11:21,133 --> 00:11:22,667
Where is your mother?

233
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:24,400
I don't know what's wrong
with your godchildren.

234
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,300
What?

235
00:11:28,433 --> 00:11:29,767
No one's going to answer?

236
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:33,400
And why did you lie to me?

237
00:11:34,967 --> 00:11:37,167
Dad, we're sorry.

238
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:38,933
We're really sorry, Dad.

239
00:11:39,067 --> 00:11:40,567
Sorry, Dad.

240
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,467
Why are you hiding her from me?

241
00:11:44,733 --> 00:11:47,233
You, Didang!

242
00:11:47,367 --> 00:11:48,633
- Didang!
- Yes, Sir?

243
00:11:48,767 --> 00:11:49,567
You know something, don't you?

244
00:11:49,700 --> 00:11:50,733
No, Sir.

245
00:11:50,867 --> 00:11:52,500
I don't know anything.

246
00:11:52,633 --> 00:11:53,767
Pinky swear, Sir.

247
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:54,667
Cross my heart.

248
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:55,500
Hope you die.

249
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:56,833
- Hey!
- Hope I die.

250
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:58,900
Jeff, call your mom.

251
00:11:59,033 --> 00:12:00,333
Come on, call her!

252
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:03,367
Jeff!

253
00:12:06,567 --> 00:12:08,167
Okay, Dad.

254
00:12:24,433 --> 00:12:24,967
Give it to me,
give it to me.

255
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:26,367
I'll talk to her.

256
00:12:28,333 --> 00:12:30,000
Aren't you going to answer that?

257
00:12:31,067 --> 00:12:34,167
They might start
asking questions.

258
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:36,767
I won't know how to answer.

259
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:43,200
I might lose control
and tell them the truth.

260
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:44,967
They won't be able to handle it.

261
00:12:45,533 --> 00:12:47,567
If you don't answer...

262
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:51,233
they'll think
you're hiding something.

263
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:58,100
Why isn't she answering?

264
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:10,167
Do you want me to answer it?

265
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:22,633
Hello, Jeffrey?

266
00:13:23,900 --> 00:13:25,333
Noah?

267
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:35,767
Friend, how are you?

268
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:44,167
I came here to apologize to you.

269
00:13:46,267 --> 00:13:47,600
I'm sorry, I messed up.

270
00:13:49,567 --> 00:13:50,500
You were right.

271
00:13:51,533 --> 00:13:53,633
I was being unreasonable.

272
00:13:53,767 --> 00:13:57,300
It's not fair to drag you
into my personal issues.

273
00:13:59,467 --> 00:14:01,367
I'm also sorry if I hurt you.

274
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:04,433
You were right to do that.

275
00:14:05,433 --> 00:14:07,400
You just slapped me
with the truth.

276
00:14:08,867 --> 00:14:10,333
But, Alice,
why is it still so hard?

277
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:13,767
It's still so hard...

278
00:14:15,233 --> 00:14:17,067
It's still so hard to accept...

279
00:14:18,233 --> 00:14:20,333
that Manuel left me again.

280
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:29,433
Why do you have Felma's phone?

281
00:14:30,467 --> 00:14:31,667
<i> Where is she?</i>

282
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:34,633
Didn't you tell Manuel
you're in Davao?

283
00:14:36,167 --> 00:14:37,467
Hindi.

284
00:14:49,333 --> 00:14:50,000
Manuel...

285
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,567
sorry about this.

286
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:54,167
Felma's busy.

287
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:56,533
She's in a meeting,
she can't be disturbed.

288
00:14:56,667 --> 00:14:58,000
Noah, I don't believe you.

289
00:14:58,133 --> 00:14:59,433
I already know
there's no conference.

290
00:14:59,567 --> 00:15:00,867
She's not in Batangas.

291
00:15:01,633 --> 00:15:03,133
Now answer me.

292
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,600
Where is she?
And why are you together?

293
00:15:05,733 --> 00:15:07,000
Aren't you in Davao?

294
00:15:09,633 --> 00:15:10,867
Jepoy, tell me.

295
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,867
What's gotten into your mom
that she suddenly

296
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,200
flew to Davao?

297
00:15:14,733 --> 00:15:16,667
We don't know either, Auntie.

298
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:17,400
What do you mean you don't know?

299
00:15:17,533 --> 00:15:19,300
Hey, hey, hey.

300
00:15:19,433 --> 00:15:20,267
What is this?

301
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:21,367
She went with Noah?

302
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:22,367
Did they run away together?

303
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:23,967
Keep your voice down, darling.

304
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:25,600
Manuel might hear you.

305
00:15:25,733 --> 00:15:26,800
Goodness gracious!

306
00:15:27,233 --> 00:15:28,433
You guys! You!

307
00:15:28,567 --> 00:15:30,600
You should've at least
warned me first.

308
00:15:30,733 --> 00:15:32,833
So we wouldn't just suddenly
show up here!

309
00:15:32,967 --> 00:15:34,933
Now it looks like
I sold out your mother!

310
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:38,667
Noah, can I talk to Felma?

311
00:15:39,867 --> 00:15:42,200
I don't even know...

312
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:43,267
what to say anymore.

313
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:45,700
I can no longer make
excuses to Manuel.

314
00:15:45,833 --> 00:15:47,567
Can you talk to him instead?

315
00:15:59,433 --> 00:16:01,067
Manuel?

316
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,367
<i> Felma?</i>

317
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,633
What's really going on?

318
00:16:04,767 --> 00:16:06,767
And why did you lie to me?

319
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:08,367
You even dragged
the kids into it.

320
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:11,667
<i> I'm sorry.</i>

321
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:14,533
Please don't be mad at them.

322
00:16:14,667 --> 00:16:15,700
<i> But why?</i>

323
00:16:15,833 --> 00:16:16,533
What's really happening?

324
00:16:16,667 --> 00:16:18,233
Where are you actually?

325
00:16:18,367 --> 00:16:20,767
And why are you with Noah?

326
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:24,533
Ah, I'm here in Davao.

327
00:16:24,667 --> 00:16:25,867
What?

328
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,533
Why did you go with him?

329
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:32,467
Because he's going
to introduce me

330
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:35,600
to a prospective investor
for the business.

331
00:16:36,367 --> 00:16:38,900
We're meeting them.

332
00:16:39,033 --> 00:16:42,433
Felma, why did you tell the kids
something else?

333
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:46,300
I didn't get the chance
to explain it to them.

334
00:16:46,433 --> 00:16:47,733
Yes, but when we talked,

335
00:16:47,867 --> 00:16:48,800
you said you had a conference.

336
00:16:48,933 --> 00:16:50,667
So what is it really?

337
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:52,133
Well...

338
00:16:52,267 --> 00:16:54,433
Conference, meeting.

339
00:16:54,567 --> 00:16:57,833
Those were what we had lined up.

340
00:16:57,967 --> 00:17:01,033
<i>I'm sorry I didn't
tell you properly.</i>

341
00:17:01,167 --> 00:17:05,900
I wanted to surprise you
and the kids...

342
00:17:07,100 --> 00:17:09,133
that the business is growing.

343
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:12,000
So when are you coming home?

344
00:17:12,133 --> 00:17:13,467
<i> It depends.</i>

345
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:15,500
If we close the deal,

346
00:17:15,667 --> 00:17:19,967
maybe tomorrow or the day after.

347
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:22,167
But I'll come home
as soon as I can.

348
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:23,333
<i> All right, okay.</i>

349
00:17:23,467 --> 00:17:25,000
Take care over there.

350
00:17:26,100 --> 00:17:27,333
I really miss you.

351
00:17:27,467 --> 00:17:28,467
<i> I miss you too, Manuel.</i>

352
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:32,033
Please take care of our kids
for now.

353
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:47,267
Dad, sorry,
we lied to you.

354
00:17:49,533 --> 00:17:51,700
You should've told me
from the start

355
00:17:51,833 --> 00:17:53,533
that your mom is in Davao.

356
00:17:54,933 --> 00:17:58,033
Dad, we just didn't want you
to get hurt.

357
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:01,667
Dear, why would I be hurt?

358
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:04,467
Because she's with Uncle Noah?

359
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:05,667
Oh.

360
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:07,200
So what?

361
00:18:08,667 --> 00:18:10,000
You're really asking that,
Manuel?

362
00:18:10,133 --> 00:18:11,200
You might get jealous.

363
00:18:11,333 --> 00:18:12,100
Come on, Manuel,

364
00:18:12,233 --> 00:18:13,000
you ask too many questions.

365
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:13,867
- Oh.
- You're talking too much...

366
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:16,567
- Oh...
- Go on and eat.

367
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:18,933
- It's good, huh?
- So good...

368
00:18:25,900 --> 00:18:27,733
But isn't it really strange?

369
00:18:30,967 --> 00:18:32,700
Auntie, Mom never mentioned

370
00:18:32,833 --> 00:18:35,400
any possible investor in Davao.

371
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:38,967
It all feels so sudden.

372
00:18:43,067 --> 00:18:45,933
- Ah.
- Come on!

373
00:18:46,067 --> 00:18:47,200
Didang!

374
00:18:47,333 --> 00:18:49,000
I'm sorry.

375
00:19:02,133 --> 00:19:05,000
Do you think Manuel believed
your alibi?

376
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:06,800
I hope so.

377
00:19:06,933 --> 00:19:09,767
I'm not used to lying to him.

378
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:12,967
He might start
suspecting something.

379
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:16,467
I'm not ready to tell him
the truth yet.

380
00:19:16,933 --> 00:19:19,233
Ah, Felma, calm down.

381
00:19:20,467 --> 00:19:22,000
He wouldn't find out

382
00:19:22,133 --> 00:19:24,033
unless we tell him.

383
00:19:24,167 --> 00:19:25,333
Or Didang does.

384
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:27,900
You reminded her, right?

385
00:19:30,433 --> 00:19:31,833
Felma, don't worry.

386
00:19:33,433 --> 00:19:35,100
Stress might just make things
worse for you.

387
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:37,767
Tell me...

388
00:19:37,900 --> 00:19:39,567
what can I do
to make you relax?

389
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:41,967
I'm okay, Noah.

390
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:46,733
Having you beside me
already means a lot.

391
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:10,833
Bro, you've officially graduated
from the wheelchair.

392
00:20:10,967 --> 00:20:14,600
Ah, those exercises really
worked.

393
00:20:14,733 --> 00:20:16,533
Even my muscles
got bigger, look!

394
00:20:16,667 --> 00:20:19,400
- Check it out.
- Ah, ah, ah.

395
00:20:19,533 --> 00:20:21,067
- Right, dear?
- Yes.

396
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:23,433
Worked for him,
not for you, dear.

397
00:20:23,567 --> 00:20:24,900
Hey, that's harsh.

398
00:20:25,033 --> 00:20:25,900
I do have some.

399
00:20:26,033 --> 00:20:26,867
- See?
- Fine, fine.

400
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:27,867
Oh!

401
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:33,500
Manuel, I just want
to say sorry.

402
00:20:33,633 --> 00:20:36,500
I'm sorry we didn't talk much.

403
00:20:36,667 --> 00:20:38,667
We just kept quiet as a couple.

404
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:42,900
Because I thought you went back
to the dwarf!

405
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:45,133
You know Felma's the only one
I love.

406
00:20:46,733 --> 00:20:49,100
I really wish she were here.

407
00:20:49,233 --> 00:20:51,767
So she could see me
walking again.

408
00:20:53,233 --> 00:20:55,233
But...

409
00:20:55,367 --> 00:20:56,733
But...

410
00:20:56,867 --> 00:21:00,967
Bro, the thing is,
she's with Noah.

411
00:21:01,633 --> 00:21:03,100
You know, Bro...

412
00:21:03,233 --> 00:21:04,667
what I'm feeling right now?

413
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:06,233
That I'm right.

414
00:21:06,367 --> 00:21:07,900
You're jealous.

415
00:21:08,033 --> 00:21:11,000
Oh... I knew it.

416
00:21:11,167 --> 00:21:12,500
Oh...

417
00:21:12,633 --> 00:21:15,967
I was just embarrassed to say it
earlier in front of the kids.

418
00:21:16,100 --> 00:21:17,833
They might think
I'm being shallow.

419
00:21:19,267 --> 00:21:21,133
But you know what?
Andrea was right.

420
00:21:22,733 --> 00:21:24,633
Felma's been impulsive lately.

421
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:29,633
And of course, the longer
she's in Davao...

422
00:21:29,767 --> 00:21:31,333
she's with Noah...

423
00:21:31,467 --> 00:21:33,933
I can't help it, I'm thinging
all sorts of things.

424
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:43,167
Sis, this wasn't sudden.

425
00:21:44,167 --> 00:21:48,500
Noah and I already talked about
the investors back in Manila.

426
00:21:49,300 --> 00:21:51,333
I just didn't mention it to you.

427
00:21:51,467 --> 00:21:54,600
So you and Noah have little
secrets now, huh?

428
00:21:54,733 --> 00:21:55,667
Wait!

429
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:57,333
What if he's just
taking advantage

430
00:21:57,467 --> 00:21:58,433
of your migraines?

431
00:21:58,567 --> 00:22:00,133
<i> Oh my! What's this,</i>

432
00:22:00,267 --> 00:22:02,733
caregiver slash lover vibes?

433
00:22:02,867 --> 00:22:04,633
<i> No, sis.</i>

434
00:22:04,767 --> 00:22:06,833
Noah is really just my friend.

435
00:22:06,967 --> 00:22:08,367
Oh my...

436
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:10,367
I still have a lot
to take care of,

437
00:22:10,500 --> 00:22:11,333
Okay?

438
00:22:11,467 --> 00:22:12,633
All right.

439
00:22:12,767 --> 00:22:14,933
Sis, just be careful over there.

440
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:17,833
Finish whatever you need to do
in Davao.

441
00:22:17,967 --> 00:22:20,167
Your family is waiting
for you here.

442
00:22:25,633 --> 00:22:27,333
What did Felma say?

443
00:22:27,467 --> 00:22:29,633
Oh, nothing really.

444
00:22:29,767 --> 00:22:32,400
She said she just has some
things to handle in Davao.

445
00:22:32,533 --> 00:22:35,833
It's purely work with Noah.

446
00:22:35,967 --> 00:22:37,800
So tell your buddy

447
00:22:37,933 --> 00:22:41,000
that he has nothing to be
jealous about.

448
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:45,900
Darling, you can't stop Manuel
from feeling that way.

449
00:22:46,033 --> 00:22:47,233
That's normal.

450
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:52,533
Hey, I'm Felma's best friend.

451
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:53,967
So if she had any secrets,

452
00:22:54,100 --> 00:22:57,467
I'd be the first to know.

453
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,967
Don't worry, bro.

454
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:02,267
You've got nothing to doubt.

455
00:23:03,667 --> 00:23:05,000
Yes, she's right.

456
00:23:10,167 --> 00:23:12,500
- Bro.
- Oh?

457
00:23:12,633 --> 00:23:14,133
Come with me to Davao.

458
00:23:14,267 --> 00:23:16,400
- Huh?
- Let's go see Felma.

459
00:23:22,333 --> 00:23:24,133
Dad, even if you don't say it,
I know you're jealous.

460
00:23:24,267 --> 00:23:25,700
What, you don't trust Mom?

461
00:23:25,833 --> 00:23:28,100
I trust your mom.

462
00:23:28,233 --> 00:23:29,067
But Noah? Sorry.

463
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:30,233
I know he's good to you, kids,

464
00:23:30,367 --> 00:23:32,900
but I don't fully trust him.

465
00:23:33,033 --> 00:23:34,467
Cheaters.

466
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:36,400
Where do you think
they're going?

467
00:23:36,533 --> 00:23:38,067
Probably on a honeymoon.

468
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:39,833
Flirty Felma's
really something, right?

469
00:23:39,967 --> 00:23:41,900
Dragging my husband
all over the place.

470
00:23:42,033 --> 00:23:43,300
So where are we going?

471
00:23:43,433 --> 00:23:46,000
I want to bring you
to the best spots in Davao.

472
00:23:46,133 --> 00:23:49,000
- Ah...
- Felma!

473
00:23:49,133 --> 00:23:50,400
Felma?

474
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:53,967
Manuel?
